> in this dropdown css class has added select2 this have to add where u want search bar in dropdown. 

 <script>
     $(document).ready(function () {
         // Check if Select2 is missing and force-load it
         if (typeof $.fn.select2 === 'undefined') {
             console.warn('Select2 is not loaded! Trying to load it now...');
             $.getScript("https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/select2/4.0.13/js/select2.min.js", function() {
                 console.log("✅ Select2 Loaded Successfully!");

                 // Initialize Select2 after loading
                 $('#VendorId').select2({
                     placeholder: "Search Vendor...",
                     allowClear: true,
                     width: "100%"
                 });
             });
         } else {
             console.log("✅ Select2 is already loaded!");

             // Initialize Select2
             $('#VendorId').select2({
                 placeholder: "Search Vendor...",
                 allowClear: true,
                 width: "100%"
             });
         }
     });
 </script>

> Add this js in same view where is your dropdown will populate below in section.

    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/select2/4.0.13/css/select2.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

> add this link in head in layout where is your view is merge.

 <!-- Load jQuery first -->
 <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.7.1/jquery.min.js"></script>

 <!-- Load Select2 -->
 <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/select2/4.0.13/js/select2.min.js"></script>

> then add this code on top of all js and jquery link in body of your layout.
